-----Original Message-----
From: Rob Berryhill <racefan@...>
To: EQ-Clerics@onelist.com <EQ-Clerics@onelist.com>
Date: Monday, July 12, 1999 3:15 PM
Subject: RE: [EQ-Clerics] soul fire


>From: "Rob Berryhill" <racefan@...>
>
>Twinking is when a high level character gives items or help to a low level
>character. To be "twinked" would mean they were items not normally
>obtainable by a character of that level.


Which, in my experience, describes most of the characters in the game right
now. Not me, but...

Makes for a lot of well-dressed corpses, as all those level 5's in full
rubicite get arrogant and try to take on stuff that is way to strong for
them. Folks in Befallen on Fennin Ro were laughing over the guy in full
rubicite dead on the second level last night.

== Gilead, dwarven cleric of Fennin Ro
